Belgian Trade Deficit Widens as December Export Growth Slows

-- B y   J o h n   M a r t e n s
-- 
2011-02-15T14:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-15/belgian-trade-deficit-widens-as-december-export-growth-slows.html
  Belgium ’s trade deficit widened to
1.5 billion euros for the first time in more than two years in
December as exports rose at the slowest pace in 10 months.  Exports from Belgium, the euro region’s sixth-largest
economy, increased 11 percent to 17.5 billion euros in December,
the nation’s central bank said today in an e-mailed statement.
Imports climbed 13 percent to 19.1 billion euros.  The December trade deficit followed a revised deficit of
553.6 million euros in November, the central bank said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
John Martens in Brussels at 
